eu.shooktea.vmsm.module.mage

Class MagentoModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.shooktea.vmsm.module.mage.MagentoModule

  • public class MagentoModule
extends java.lang.Object
    Representation of single module installed on Magento.

    Every module in Magento is stored in one of three code pools: core, community and local. Core code pool is a base of Magento and shouldn't be edited by module programmers. Community code pool contains modules downloaded for free or bought on Magento repository or other webpages. Local code pool contains modules used only in current installation of Magento.

    Modules' full names consists of two parts connected by underscore, i.e. Mage_Adminhtml. First part is module's namespace and second is module's name.

    Every module has a version saved in configuration file and in database. If these two version are not equal, setup script is launched to update module to newer version.
